{
  "texts": [
    "Those who are already strongly committed to a view are more likely to generate objections against popular opinions that conflict with theirs and to be reinforced in their own view.",
    "What stands out from these findings is that polls trigger internal deliberation, especially on the part of the not-too involved, yet still attentive citizens.",
    "If we follow this theory, cue-giving is not about uncritical endorsement, rather the opposite.",
    "Coming back to the example of the voter from rural France, the newly acquired knowledge about the political preferences of the neighbourhood should make you think further.",
    "If you are strongly committed to the far left, you are likely to generate further objections against the right."
  ]
}